(1087, 1242341605, NULL, 1242309600, '1', 1, 4, 'C', '6, 8, 10, 14, etc ', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 6, 'Todays paper has some severe show through. Also the black laydown looks like it is suffering from poor water/ink balance. Excesive setoff was also noted.\r\nCould we have some feedback on this issue please? Are we running too much water generally? would the show through be less apparent with less water etc? ', 15, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nThe show through is evident in our copies mostly on pages that have solid red on opposite side, I have spoken with Mick; he is going to speak with Greg Wood. \r\nAs we are experiencing the same concerns with Cumberland we may have to begin talks with paper, ink and solution people to access if it is just the paper or is there anything else that is causing the show through. We are going to get Norske to measure the opacity of 45 to 42 (which they currently measure for us)\r\n\r\nGary\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
