(1101, 1247032840, NULL, 1246888800, '1', 3, 1, 'D', '28', '', '', 'TPG', '', 1, 11, 1, 9, 'TPG have noticed their ad appeared blue instead of purple. This is repeat material and therefore should have run the same colour. We require ASAP quantities of effected books and also some good copies if they are available.\r\nThis is quite urgent.\r\nThanks.', 5, NULL, 'The check copies indicate all copies have printed slightly more blue than the proof, however, this is very slight.\r\nPlease note, there were no grey bars on this page, therefore, the team had no accurate tool to set the density.\r\nPlease send your complaint copy for further assessment.\r\n', 'Closed', '', 'quantity of run', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1102, 1248414161, NULL, 1248184800, '2', 16, 1, 'F', '34', 'Professionals', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'Professional ad on page 34, their corporate colour Red printed Orange.', 5, NULL, 'Checked the check copies poor colour balance is evident from start up to 70,000 then copies came good this was at the switch to the Holroid edition change', 'Closed', '', '70,000', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1103, 1248414846, NULL, 1248444000, '1', 12, 1, '', 'all', '', '', 'production', '', 0, 7, 1, 22, 'black lay down is not good very chalky,causing pages to look ghosted, soft and noisy', 5, NULL, 'I have checked all the check copies and poor ink coverage is consistent throughout the run. a complete set proofs are supplied to press crews for Home magazine, Espon proofer needs to be re-linearized as colour does not match Holt Street supplied proofs\r\n\r\nGary W', 'Closed', '', 'all at holt street', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1104, 1249365143, NULL, 1248962400, '2', 12, 1, 'E', '11', 'Panthers', '', 'Two Dogs Agency', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'Hi\r\n\r\nClient has 2 complaints about their ad. First complaint is the colour. Meant to be a teal colour but has printed Green. Second is the background watermark not appearing. But I have explained to the client the way they set up the ad was incorrect for a watermark effect.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nLee', 11, NULL, 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nUnfortunately we could not locate the check copies for this run. we can estimate if this problem was throughout the complete run.\r\n\r\nSimon doherty has reviewed the check copy process and will be monitoring which crews are not keeping check copies\r\n\r\nGary ', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1105, 1249864333, NULL, 1249135200, '1', 8, 1, '', '5', '', '', 'David Jones', '', 1, 7, 1, 9, 'Client is complaining that the print is washed out lacking Cyan, Gary Woodside will be bringing in the proof and print.\r\n\r\nCan we find out how many were affected plus why, how and what the usual?\r\nCan we find out today please?\r\nIf you put a proof out you will see the problem', 26, NULL, 'This problem was evident throughout all the check copies, density was checked and within range. A test re run of this page is required to check plates are holding the dot.\r\n\r\nThis page was re-run on press 18/8/09 in a test scenario running the same plate configuration running on the same plate line and the same press unit, the white type was visible on this test. Unfortunately there is no evidence as to what caused this on the night, there were no other scenarios to highlight that there were problems with the other plates on the night.', 'Closed', '', 'many', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1106, 1250463942, NULL, 1250172000, '2', 12, 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 15, 2, 12, 'driver left with 20 bulk short 2000 copies', 0, NULL, 'investigated further with the shortage of Penrith Press and can only come to the conclusion of the following. \r\n\r\n1. The run was rather messy with a high volume of winding on.\r\n\r\n2. Approximately 4000 came down the FAT which was a lengthy process through the run and at the end to hand repair.\r\n\r\n3. Possibly with no conclusion some of the new casuals might have made up bulk of the wrong size.\r\n\r\n4. Unwinding approx 14500 takes quite a long time which meant hanging onto the press as long as we could. The call was made to knock the press nearing the end so that it could change over to the next product.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAll staff concerned was engaged in other editions and tasks as well as Penrith Press, possibly next time if this situation arises we will inflate the spoilage so that the target is met and dump what ever over’s there are. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nKind Regards\r\n Paul Cleary\r\n', 'Closed', '', '2000', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1107, 1251176481, NULL, 1251122400, '1', 1, 4, 'D', 'all', 'Geoff Booth', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 23, 'It has been noted that the DT on D press today has some major setoff issues. Could we have a figure on how many were effected and why?\r\nThanks.', 14, NULL, 'The set-off throughout the book was the result of a build up on the folder nip rollers not being cleaned.\r\nThe set-off started at around 70,000 on D press, therefore, 50,000 copies were affected = 13%.\r\nThis will be discussed with the responsible night shift team.\r\nAt this stage we clean this on an as needs basis, as the build depends on the amount of ink on page 1.\r\nThis is one of the best examples of this build we have seen, therefore, pages of the paper will be scanned and used for training purposes and determining an additional regular cleaning ycle.\r\nMick', 'Closed', '', '50,000', '0', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1108, 1251786798, NULL, 1252072800, '1', 2, 4, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 1, 5, 3, 'TWAM\r\n3 reels out of 20 supplied by Hannan Print were sent back as these were unsatisfactory ', 0, NULL, '', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1109, 1251790041, NULL, 1250863200, '1', 2, 4, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 1, 5, 3, 'TWAM\r\n2 reels out of 20 supplied by Hannan Print. John Williams from Hannan came to Chullora to inspect poor quality reels action plan put in place to inspect each week and reject bad reels back to Hannan to be rewound', 0, NULL, '', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1110, 1252045841, NULL, 1252072800, '1', 12, 1, 'C', 'Through out', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 1, 17, 'Hi There,\r\nConcerns over line ups through out the mag a just a few pages had rego issues.\r\n\r\nCopy sent into Gary pages marked.\r\n\r\nThanks', 1, '14', 's  	Registration problems were experienced at the start of the run. Standard adjustments were unsuccessful - plates were changed to rectify. Our check copies indicate the page 11 ad was .5mm out (cyan magenta to yellow black) for 57,000 / 20% copies affected. We have just received the complaint copy where the rego is out 1mm and the page alignment is poor - none of our check copies are this bad, however, we don\\''t have any check copies before 38K, therefore, the assumption is 30,000 / 10% copies were affected at the start of the run. Mick', 'Closed', '', 'QC copies', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1111, 1252277627, NULL, 1252072800, '1', 12, 1, 'C', '11 (+others)', '', '', 'Cosmopolitan Homes', '', 1, 11, 1, 5, 'Cosmopolitan Homes has noticed that their ad on page 11 of the Homes mag is blurry (registration) and also trims off at the bottom.\r\nWe require a quantity as they are chasing compensation for this ad.\r\n', 7, NULL, 's  	Registration problems were experienced at the start of the run. Standard adjustments were unsuccessful - plates were changed to rectify. Our check copies indicate the page 11 ad was .5mm out (cyan magenta to yellow black) for 57,000 / 20% copies affected. We have just received the complaint copy where the rego is out 1mm and the page alignment is poor - none of our check copies are this bad, however, we don''t have any check copies before 38K, therefore, the assumption is 30,000 / 10% copies were affected at the start of the run. Mick', 'Closed', 'Day', '57,000', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1112, 1252375088, NULL, 1252332000, '1', 1, 4, 'C', '3, 7, 8, 9, ', 'Geoff Booth', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 9, 'page 3: reversing shadows in jeans. Cyan and Magenta desity high.\r\npage 7: main image reversing shadows, very yellow. Black density low. Yellow high.\r\npage 8: pic in ad warm. Magenta density high.\r\npage 9: main image. poor original. magenta slightly high.\r\npage 18: Rove image. poor separation.\r\npage 35: Adrian Bower image. poor separation.\r\n\r\nSome fit issues also. ', 5, NULL, 'Density readings taken on all pages highlighted \r\n\r\nAfter consultation we feel that the optimum print would have been somewhere in between the two samples provided.\r\n\r\nFindings below:\r\n\r\nIssue page 3: \r\n\r\n•	GB’s copy: Black density is slightly down the grey bean is not too unbalanced, due to a lot of cyan in the separation (in the jeans area) unfortunately this is dominating causing the reversing affect\r\n\r\nIssue page 7: \r\n\r\n•	In both copies the black density in down through the middle and bottom of the page, yellow is noticible high but no grey beans in the centre for cross reference, printer should have made better judgement to reduce yellow\r\n\r\nIssue page 8: \r\n•	GB’s copy: Readings indicate that Magenta density is .07 over optimum (too high)\r\n\r\n\r\nIssue page 9: \r\n\r\n•	GB’s copy: grey bean slightly warm, Black density on both copies within range\r\n\r\n\r\nIssue page 18: \r\n\r\n•	Imaging\r\n\r\nIssue page 35:.\r\n\r\n•	Imaging   (fit is slightly off)\r\n\r\nWhile we are in the process of implementing densitometers which will aid in achieving better balance, currently it is purely a visual checking process. \r\nI will reaffirm with press team leaders whenever they notice this reversing issue that this due to the black ink running low and needs to be fixed.\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1113, 1252456083, NULL, 1252418400, '1', 1, 4, 'C', '8, 13, 20, 30, 35, ', 'Geoff Booth', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 5, 'FYI\r\nAll QC copies recieved into Holt street had registration issues throughout. \r\nPlease be aware that these copies are scutinised by the GM and the MD.\r\n', 10, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nI have gone through all 13 check copies taken from 12.45am – 3.15am on C press there are no signs of registration problems on all check copies. The pages highlighted were on the same side of the web (press configuration included in email to you).\r\n\r\nWe will need to view the copy you have sent to us, we can only assume that when the QC''s were called that unfortunately publishing may have taken these copies after a web join has gone through. \r\n\r\nWe are reviewing the process of having a press operator check the bundles on the publishing floor before dispatching.\r\n\r\nAfter viewing the QC copies this is evident that a web join had gone through at the time the Holt Street bundles were tagged', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1114, 1254117181, NULL, 1253800800, '2', 19, 1, 'F', '', '', '', 'Response Raine and Horne', '', 1, 3, 2, 13, 'Hi Gary\r\n\r\nI received some complaints with the trimming of the Penrith Press Real Estate.\r\n\r\nI''ve had a look at the check copies and the trim marks don''t align throughout the run.\r\n\r\nThanks', 16, NULL, 'After receiving client copy, it is evident that this is start up copy. as all check copies indicate there is no movement vertically. There was some movement between the 2 webs horizontally. based on these check copies this indicates that start up copies have made it into live production. Press crews have been made aware that when QC''s are ready to be taken that a press operator must physically check the copies that Publishing are taking as QC''s', 'Closed', '', '', '1', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1115, 1254184848, NULL, 1254146400, '2', 18, 1, '', '3 and 5', '', '', '', '', 0, 1, 2, 14, ' The Hillshire for the 29th Sept had a 4 page wrap around the main book. Pages A-2, A-3 and A-4 were correct, however the A-1 page looks to be incorrect and should have been the page 1 for the main book, so therefore has affected page 3 and 5. Samples left on your desk.\r\n\r\nPress crews alerted me to the problem after running approx 2500 copies and pulled up until I could investigate. I spoke to Ron in the plate room and then rang Manny in at ECD who then informed me that we do not handle the Hillshire. Manny then gave me the number for a Ray Briggs ( I think that was his last name ) I explained the situation and he told me that nothing could be done at this hour and run on. I also rang Lee Dunks but only got his voicemail.\r\n\r\nSo as a result all 65,000 copies will be incorrect. Is there an after hours contact number in case of further issues.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nScott. ', 27, NULL, 'Files were incorrectly sent from Cumberland Production', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1116, 1258069933, NULL, 1258030800, '1', 1, 4, 'D', 'throughout', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 7, 'It was noted that the DT, cf edition on D press was very flat and dull throughout.\r\nI will send a copy and also proofs to Gary Woodside for investigation and feedback.', 11, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nat the time of investigation, I could not locate check copies for this particular issue.\r\n\r\n', 'Closed', '', 'all recieved', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1117, 1260837892, NULL, 1260795600, '1', 1, 4, 'D', '8, 17,22, (62,63)', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 9, 'Today''s paper had quite a few pages where the black wasn''t up to density. As you would be aware this causes a poor reproduction in conjunction with opti-ink.\r\nYou can see the effects of this on certain colours more than others eg: P17.\r\n\r\nPlease make the teams aware that the black laydown and water balance is crucial to a quality book.\r\nThanks.', 5, NULL, 'After  checking the file copies on D press; it seems more evident on p8 and 17 the black is down between 0.88 and 0.94 not as bad on p22 62-63 \r\n\r\n We will re-highlight the importance of the black density especially when you see the reversing scenario \r\n\r\nRegards Gary\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1118, 1260846768, NULL, 1260277200, '2', 1, 1, 'C', '48', 'Gosford Council', '', 'Archibald Prize', '', 1, 3, 2, 2, 'Hi Gary\r\n\r\nI recieved a compliant from the client regarding the Black looking washed out on their ad. I took a densitometer reading and the reading varied between .76 to .8 which is quite low.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nLee', 5, NULL, 'The ad did run light for the first 5,000 copies due to an ad on the other collect page stipping the ink out. The black was increased significantly, however, was still slightly low in density for the entire run.\r\nI will need a the actual copy to accurately determine the extent of the problem.\r\nMick.E', 'Closed', '', 'All', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1119, 1265351291, NULL, 1265288400, '2', 2, 1, 'e', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 9, 'Gary\r\n\r\nReceived a compalint internally regarding the print quality of the South edition Central Coast. There is a lot set off throughout the book, i did notice it on press at around 26,000 into the run and got the guys to back off the crush which fixed it straight away.\r\n\r\nLee', 14, NULL, 'Lee,\r\n\r\nThe set-off is evident in the check copies until the 28,000 3rd check copy. I have spoken to the team and highlighted the importance of keeping an eye on set off and do what ever means possible to reducing this whilst still maintaining good colour balance. Paying extra attention to the amount of crush applied to all jobs.\r\n\r\n ', 'Closed', '', '26,000', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1121, 1283833212, NULL, 1283781600, '2', 11, 1, 'E', '17', '', '', 'Harris Farm Markets', '', 0, 3, 2, 6, 'Hi Gary\r\n\r\nThe Harris farm ad on page 17 is off registration on the bottom half of the page, which is affecting there reverse type in the banner. Being that this was the QC copies i wanted to know if that was the best result the press could do and if the entire run is like this?\r\nHarris Farm are one of the main clients that advertise in a lot of our pubs, so when i was on the press i would usually make sure there pages received a bit more attention, and if it meant getting there page on registration would put another page out i would prefer that. Most of the guys on the press would probably know that anyway.\r\nThanks, Lee Dunks', 7, NULL, 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nI have checked all check copies and this problem is evident throughout the run. Garth feels this is a bustle wheel adjustment required and will speak with the respective press crew involved highlighting the importance of this customer. If this is avoidable through this bustle wheel adjustments I would prefer to put the focus on this setting not just this client to avoid any further complaints form other clients \r\n\r\nthanks Gary', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1122, 1284525734, NULL, 1284472800, '2', 22, 1, 'E', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 9, 'Hi Gary\r\n\r\nThere is a lot off set off throughout the entire book. Usually set off like this is the result of dirty nips, it\\''s mainly in the center of the pages.\r\n\r\nIs the whole run like this?\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nLee Dunks', 1, '1', 'All check copies had minimal sign off set-off, did show some sign if show though but pages did not appear to be over inked. when looking at Lee\\''s copies there was some setting off, this may have been due to extra pressure once bundled in publishing. after further investigation it was noticed that a few pages were running 400% black in the original supplied PDF. Lee to investigate from CNG end. plate templates had bypassed OPTI in which should convert. it must be noted that OPTI inks intention is not to catch out of specification files\r\n\r\nGary', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1123, 1287467689, NULL, 1287493200, '2', 6, 1, 'C', '15', '', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 11, 'Gary\r\n\r\nReceived a customer complaint from Centro, there is Cyan image missing throughout their ad. Another ad, CUA, is also missing image but haven''t received a complaint from them yet. Also the classifieds on page 90 is missing image and you can not read the reverse text inside the blue boxes.\r\n\r\nIs the whole run like this?\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nLee', 29, NULL, 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nAfter speaking with printers responsible for running the Blacktown Advocate, there is no justifiable excuse for this error. \r\n\r\nThe standard 15 minute check copies were taken for the duration of the run. \r\n\r\nWhile performing these checks the printers responsible have been complacent with their quality checks and not picked up the error of inconstant cyan ink lay down\r\n\r\nThis has been addressed with the printers responsible who understand the quality expectations, they take full responsibility for this error, and a performance warning letter will be issued and kept on record.\r\n\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Printing Operations Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1124, 1291179571, NULL, 1291122000, '1', 2, 4, 'C', '10', '', '', 'TPG', '', 1, 11, 1, 9, 'The full page ad On page 10 "TPG" has been flagged by the client as the wrong colour. ie: too blue. I have looked at the copy we have here and I can see that the Cyan is over density. Could we get Numbers etc and flag this with the press crew to keep an eye on in future.\r\nThanks.', 5, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nI have checked all check copies taken every 10,000 copies. Unfortunately all copies appear on the bluer side of purple; this is evident throughout the entire run of 46,000 copies.\r\n\r\nI will address this issue with the press crew responsible; unfortunately this colour 100m60c30k can tend to shift on the blue side if the cyan ink is slightly high or the magenta slightly low.\r\n\r\nMoving forward when advertising has this client booked if Chullora plate room can be notified so a hard proof of this advert can be supplied to the press for colour matching\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1);
INSERT INTO `qcc_qcissues` (`qcc_id`, `qcc_logdate`, `qcc_responsedate`, `qcc_pubdate`, `qcc_company`, `qcc_publication`, `qcc_edition`, `qcc_press`, `qcc_pageno`, `qcc_agent`, `qcc_agentphone`, `qcc_client`, `qcc_clientphone`, `qcc_reporttype`, `qcc_operator`, `qcc_department`, `qcc_errortype`, `qcc_errordetails`, `qcc_errorresponse`, `qcc_respondingmanager`, `qcc_responsedetails`, `qcc_status`, `qcc_presscrew`, `qcc_copiesaffected`, `qcc_dayshift`, `qcc_afternoonshift`, `qcc_nightshift`, `qcc_submitted`, `qcc_responseemailsent`) VALUES
(1125, 1291852290, NULL, 1291726800, '1', 3, 1, 'D', '20', '', '', 'Bridge Climb', '', 1, 11, 1, 5, 'The client has contacted us regarding the registration of the ad on the bottom of page 20. Can we get numbers etc.\r\nThanks.', 0, NULL, 'Checked the QC copies in the quietroom and there were minor issues with fan in a the bottom of page 20 that have caused minor rego problems to the bridge climb add that was consistant for the majority of the production run. This issue has been brought to the attention of the press crew involved.', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1126, 1293067019, NULL, 1293022800, '1', 1, 4, 'D', '35, 36, 39 ', '', '', '', '', 0, 17, 1, 5, 'Over the past couple of days the rego on Race Form of the Telegraph has been out considerably(on 23/12/10 -between 1 to 3 dots out).\r\n', 7, NULL, 'After looking at check copies from D press there are some check copies showing signs of slight rego mostly on the black.There is a 141,000 check copy which appears to be out by 2 dots. Gary will raise this with the shift supervisors to have the printers keep an eye on this.\r\n Gary\r\n \r\n\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1127, 1296086923, NULL, 1295960400, '2', 16, 1, 'C', '50-51', '', '', 'LJ Hooker', '', 1, 3, 2, 15, 'Hi Gary\r\nLJ Hooker have complained about their Butt to Gutter advertisement not butting together, which it isn''t. \r\nIt looks like the Press haven''t adjusted the fold to butt the ads up??\r\nI''ve checked our documentation we send Swamy and it is marked Butt to Gutter on pages 50-51\r\nThanks\r\nLee', 30, NULL, 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nI have spoken with ATL who ran the Parramatta, he indicated that the job was running into the pins and did not have much room to move the pages across.\r\n\r\nAfter looking at the copies there is a slight LAP of about 2mm which could have been reduced, this would have  provided some more room to move the whole page to the right 2mm which would have assisted in achieving a but to gutter.\r\n\r\nI have highlighted to the ATL responsible that they must refer to the paper work, doing what they can to achieve a better but to gutter \r\n\r\nThe slight white gap in the centre is evident through out the run\r\n\r\nregards Gary\r\n', 'Closed', '', 'Whole Run', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1128, 1296521132, NULL, 1295874000, '1', 3, 1, '?', '20', '', '', 'Travelscene', '', 1, 11, 1, 16, 'The ad at the bottom of the page has poor registration and also Black image missing in the red background.\r\nCould we get numbers effected please.\r\nThanks.', 31, NULL, 'Hi Scott, \r\n\r\nWhen looking at our check copies there is evidence of blanket damage in this area of the Travel Scene Advertisement \r\n\r\nMx is run in Straight mode, the problem of missing image is evident on every 2nd check copy.\r\n\r\nThis means approximately 50,000 copies would have this problem.\r\n\r\nI will highlight this to the press crew Team Leader, to place greater focus on the quality reproduction especially on Adverting pages\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Printing Operations Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1129, 1299472520, NULL, 1298466000, '1', 3, 1, 'C', '10', '', '', 'Travelscene', '', 0, 11, 1, 5, 'Travelscene ad is very poor rego on the client copy. Can we get number effected ASAP thanks.', 11, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nUnfortunately there are no check copies in the designated shelf for this day; this will be taken up with the Team Leader on C press dayshift\r\n\r\nRegards Gary', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1130, 1300749259, NULL, 1300626000, '1', 3, 1, 'D', '15', '', '', 'Uniting care', '', 0, 3, 1, 3, 'The client has noticed their copy has the rego (black) out quite a bit. can we get numbers effected.\r\nThanks.', 1, '40', 'Hi Scott and Aleks\r\n\r\nWe have gone through the check copies, the start up check appears OK the following 10,000 copy is OK.  Just after this 10,000 check copy the press crew noticed registration on page 4 drifting out, this was identified as a plate slipping. \r\n\r\nThe quad tech unit then drove out, as it was trying to compensate for the slipped plate, this affected other pages on this print unit including page 15\r\n\r\nPage 4 plate was changed, which rectified the problem\r\n\r\nThis was noticed just after the 20,000 check copy and only affected minimal copies as the 30,000 and following check copies all appear good.\r\n\r\nRegards, Gary\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1131, 1302137490, NULL, 1302098400, '2', 17, 1, 'D', '17-18, 19-20', '', '', '', '', 0, 1, 3, 12, 'Found pages doubled up on 17 and 19 pages were identical as well as 18 and 20 were identical. Call Cumberland to inform them of pages doubled up which resulted in a late start off the press due to new pages coming through again. Pages were found during Make Ready and no good copies went out.', 32, NULL, 'mistake sent by CNG', 'Closed', '', 'Nil', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1132, 1306817607, NULL, 1306677600, '1', 3, 1, 'F', '3', '', '', 'Clearly contacts', '', 1, 11, 1, 24, 'Guys, we need numbers on the catchup page 3. \r\nobviously the client on page 3 was the one that flagged it with us but we will prob get more complaints. They have copies from multiple locations and the ones we got in the building are the same.\r\n\r\nThe catchup is throughout the book on different colours....... what happened?', 1, NULL, 'Scott,\r\nI have chased this up at our end with the colour hand involved and he idicated to me that he did have some issues with catch-up during the run and was continually upping the water values, he has assured me that there was no way it was throughout the entire run. \r\nI went to check the check copies for Mondays run and they were all gone. This has started to become a problem for us as they keep getting taken for reading and not returned. This issue is also being addressed.\r\nI was able to get a bulk from publishing and there were no catch-up issues in those copies. Sorry but I can''t give you a figure on how many were affected.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat we have done:\r\nWe have checked the techno on Freddy press and there are no issues with the treated water it is supplying to the press.\r\nI have arranged for a bulk of MX copies to be left in the quiet room of the MX press each day to hopefully stop the check coipes from disappearing. I will take further action if this does not solve the problem.\r\nI have asked Shaw the dayshift TL to ensure that a press operator checks the QC copies in publishing each day, as this is supposed to be what happens anyway.\r\nWe are also in the process of speaking to all the dayshift printers to ensure that MX along with all products are printed at the consistant high standard that we all expect.\r\nPlease let me know if you need anything else.\r\nRegards\r\nSteve Hainsworth\r\nDayshift Pressroom manager', 'Closed', '', 'all', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1133, 1308627225, NULL, 1308578400, '2', 18, 1, 'C', '35 - 46', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 10, '10 bundles of 25 which came back to Cumberland as the QC coies have Magenta Catch up on the entire spread of 35-46. It looks like start up copies and these were used as QC copies, so not sure if the QC copies were taken?\r\n\r\nThanks, Lee', 1, '1', 'Unfortunately this was never resolved, \r\n\r\nInitially thought start up copies got sent as QC’s, we were advised that the QC process was followed correctly and no indication in press reports of start up problems\r\n\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1135, 1308797096, NULL, 1308232800, '1', 3, 1, 'D', '24', '', '', 'TPG', '', 1, 11, 1, 9, 'The full page TPG ad that appears on the back page has reproduced dark Blue again. This issue has been flagged before and will need to be re-visited.\r\nThe client is one of the MX''s main clients and are not happy with the inconsistency of their corporate colour between print sites.\r\nThe brand manager is requiring an explanation and a action plan that will help placate the client and reduce the likelihood of repeat issues.\r\nThanks', 5, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nIt was evident that all the Chullora check copies were leaning towards the bluer side of purple, especially when comparing to the sample you provided printed by the Victoria site\r\n\r\nWhen comparing both copies to the supplied proof Victoria’s version seemed too purple and Chullora too blue, in between the two would be the ideal colour match\r\n\r\nSince the complaint we have laminated copies of the TPG proof and placed this in all press quiet rooms, an email will follow to all press team leaders instructing them to tool box talk this recent complaint and to be diligent with the ongoing colour matching of TPG material in all publications\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n___________________________________________________________________________\r\n', 'Closed', '', '?', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1136, 1309500982, NULL, 1309442400, '2', 2, 2, '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 6, 'There are a few pages that Cyan is out of registration. I have spoken to Gary Woodside regarding this already.\r\n\r\nThe edition is actually the Central Coast Real Estate, but their was no edition to select in the drop down for publication. Might need Steve Mather to add this edition.\r\n\r\nThanks Lee', 8, NULL, 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nAfter speaking with Dayshift Team Leader, C press was encountering registration problems with one Cyan unit yesterday from the beginning of the run. Normally when registration problems occur with the automatic registration system (quadtech) the system can be run in manual mode to enable the production run to be completed. \r\n\r\nWhen running the Real Estate in manual yesterday the Cyan registration kept driving out, later a faulty quadtech camera was identified and replaced. \r\n\r\n\r\nThroughout all the press stop / starts (which I have extracted from press report shown below) copies are run to waste while troubleshooting, with yesterdays run equating to 11,700 waste copies which we normally total 2,000-3,000 waste copies. We believe that when stopping the press each time a small number of copies make it into the good copy stream unfortunately ending up in the main book.\r\n\r\nI have gone through all check copies kept for this run, 10k, 15k, 20k, 25k, 30k, 40k, 50k all copies show no signs of this error, you are more than welcome to collect these press check copies to show the client if required.\r\n\r\nExtract from “production report”:\r\nHigh waste due to rego driving out and staple problems. Camera found to be faulty on unit 1, replaced with no further problems\r\n\r\nTime stamps from stops in “Press Report”:\r\n4.51am Numerous stops due to cyan driving away on unit-1, dumped at waste 2.\r\n\r\n5.00am Electrician called to reboot unit-1 pc-2, had to manually move rego. Scanner not locking on.\r\n\r\n5.24am Rego out again, console screen and units froze on units-1 and 2, electricians called, and told me that there was a system upgrade this morning causing disruption to the quadtechs and computer.\r\n\r\n6.53am Rego out in manual, reset quad tech''s\r\n\r\n7.09am Rego driving out in manual mode, recall job, call electrical\r\n\r\n7.19am Rego still out, electrical rebooted quad tech''s, job recalled again,\r\n\r\n7.44am Rego still out, electrical replaced camera 2 in unit 1\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1137, 1310102250, NULL, 1310133600, '1', 14, 1, 'D', '8-9', '', '', '', '', 0, 6, 3, 11, 'error need to edit \r\n\r\nWeekend Professional page CA 8 and CA 9 are numbered page 2 & 3\r\n\r\n', 1, '8', 'Gents,\r\n\r\nBy next Wednesday I’m aiming to have a check list for every newsprint product we produce. Showing what’s been checked and who has done it.\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nJohn Arakelian\r\n', 'Closed', '', '0', '0', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1138, 1311116704, NULL, 1310220000, '1', 13, 3, 'E', '98', '', '', '', '', 0, 6, 3, 11, 'folio mistake caught by press on Sunday Tele 10th July page 98 the date line was the previous week 3.7.2011,\r\n', 1, '8', 'Gents,\r\n\r\nBy next Wednesday I’m aiming to have a check list for every newsprint product we produce. Showing what’s been checked and who has done it.\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nJohn Arakelian\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
