(1140, 1311310765, NULL, 1311429600, '1', 13, 2, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 6, 3, 11, 'I have another error in the index of Shopper. I rang Mark Soulie\r\nat 5:40 am to let him know that it had been picked up on press\r\nand we would continue to run P421 & 422 instead of 21 & 22 repeated \r\n12 times in a column.\r\n\r\n Damo\r\n\r\n', 1, '8', 'New checking process in place at Holt Street', 'Closed', '', '120000', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1141, 1312179997, NULL, 1312120800, '1', 2, 4, 'E', '40', '', '', 'Darley', '', 1, 14, 1, 12, 'The Darley ad on the bottom of page 40 has a small amount of blanket damage above the D of the logo in the bottom right hand corner. Just need to know how many copies are effected.', 31, NULL, 'Hi Angus,\r\n\r\nI have checked all check copies throughout the run and there is evidence of Cyan blanket damage, it appears that the blanket damage is also evident the following week as the job has been printed on the same press with the exact same press set-up.\r\n\r\nI had the dayshift printers examine the blanket in relation to press unit position in question and could not immediate identify any damage; I then had them remove and change the blanket.\r\n\r\nAfter closer inspection of the blanket, there is a small soft spot in the coresponfiding area where this page would have printed.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately this problem is evident throughout the entire run of approximately 55,000 copies for both consecutive weeks. I discussed this issue and left samples with Damien Zahra - Press Operations Manager who will follow this up with the appropriate printers who printed this product, highlighting the importance of identifying and rectifying blanket damage \r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '1', 1, 1),
(1142, 1312765606, NULL, 1312725600, '1', 2, 4, 'C', '40', '', '', 'Darley', '', 1, 14, 1, 12, 'The Darley ad on the bottom of page 40 has a small amount of blanket damage above the D of the logo in the bottom right hand corner. Just need to know how many copies are effected. \r\n\r\nThis is the second week in a row, same size and spot .', 31, NULL, 'Hi Angus,\r\n\r\nI have checked all check copies throughout the run and there is evidence of Cyan blanket damage, it appears that the blanket damage is also evident the following week as the job has been printed on the same press with the exact same press set-up.\r\n\r\nI had the dayshift printers examine the blanket in relation to press unit position in question and could not immediate identify any damage; I then had them remove and change the blanket.\r\n\r\nAfter closer inspection of the blanket, there is a small soft spot in the coresponfiding area where this page would have printed.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately this problem is evident throughout the entire run of approximately 55,000 copies for both consecutive weeks. I discussed this issue and left samples with Damien Zahra - Press Operations Manager who will follow this up with the appropriate printers who printed this product, highlighting the importance of identifying and rectifying blanket damage \r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '1', 1, 1),
(1143, 1312932227, NULL, 1314540000, '1', 4, 1, 'E', '1', '', '', 'Paper customer', '', 1, 7, 1, 15, 'Hi Gary,\r\nI have received a complaint about the print of the Sportsman 29th July E press, the customer purchased this paper in Victoria the outer cover is off centre by 2cms. Certain detail listings a missing about a cm.\r\nThe customer complaint was that he was unable to read particular results hence hindered his ability to make an informed decisions on certain races.\r\n', 33, NULL, 'After investigation of sample provided, this appears to be a bubble in the folder on the outside web.\r\n\r\nThere was no problems recorded on the press report for this production run   \r\n\r\nThis would have only affected 50 or so copies as the bubble would have corrected itself very quickly, \r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1144, 1313022269, NULL, 1312552800, '1', 12, 1, '', '14-15', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 18, 'Centre spread Magenta plate worn.', 34, NULL, 'Hi Scott,\r\n\r\nAfter looking at all check copies for this issue of Home Magazine, the problem started to appear around the 166,000 mark to about 230,000 then  was much more evident all the way to 335,993, this has been identified as an image wear problem affecting over 100,000 copies\r\n\r\nDamien has discussed  the issue with the press crew responsible and is raising awareness with shift Managers and TL’s to download to their\r\nteams.\r\n\r\nWe are currently experiencing some issues with the new inks causing excessive plate wear, which is being investigated. As an interim solution on larger print runs two sets of plates will be provided for press crews to perform full changes over half way through these production runs to avoid quality issue related to image wear  \r\n\r\nApologies for any inconvenience caused, you feedback assists us greatly highlighting any quality issues\r\n\r\nGary\r\n', 'Closed', '', '100.000', '0', '0', '1', 1, 1),
(1145, 1314665157, NULL, 1314280800, '2', 2, 1, 'D', '10-15', 'Brian Hilton Toyota', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'Gary, page 10-15 of the motor section in Central Coast has 2 Magenta plates, and the result is no yellow image on the page.\r\n', 1, '1', 'Visual check with Arkitex has been implemented for all Hybrid and two page spreads on start up. Procedure has been implemented and toolboxed. DZ\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1149, 1315525921, NULL, 1315231200, '2', 17, 1, 'D', '29', '', '', 'Spurling', '', 1, 3, 2, 6, 'Bottom half of page 29 on CCN copies are out of registration, Customer complained that their copy was out of registration, they said it was like this last week also. Was the entire run like this?', 1, '1', 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nThere is evidence of slight registration issues on the Spurling Advert, after further investigation this reverse white type is well below the minimum 8 point type specified in the Cumberland advertisement specifications. The type in mention is under 2mm in height, 8 point type should measure approximately 0.35mm.\r\n\r\nThe press crews endeavour to minimise registration problems but reverse type this small is very hard to control \r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1150, 1315529440, NULL, 1314885600, '2', 19, 1, 'D', '3, 12, 17, 33, 44, 49, 58', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 6, 'A few pages in Penrith Press are out of registration. I have received a copy from an internal rep or a client which I can sent to someone if needed. Please check if check copies are showing any registration issues.', 1, '1', 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nThe check copies do not appear to have registration problems which you mentioned over the phone, I will wait to see your copy on Wednesday \r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1151, 1316647757, NULL, 1316440800, '1', 3, 1, 'F', '8', '', '', 'UTS Insearch', '', 1, 7, 1, 23, 'A complaint has been fielded by Tammy regarding the reproduction of the UTS ad on Page 8, alll copies here plus the clients copies have excessive set off across ormage baxk ground from the opposing page.', 1, '1', 'Hi Mark\r\n\r\nWe received your copy of Mx which does show signs of set-off. \r\n\r\nWe have gone through the press check copies there is a slight gripper mark at the centre of the page on the spine side which is hard to avoid due to the dark image on the opposite page transferring some ink. The check copy at 21,000 appears to have slightly more of a gripper mark and some slight set-off, but the remainder of the check copies appear good.\r\n\r\nYou copy appears worse than our 21,000 check copy which would be due to the fact that when these copies are bulked up in publishing the pressure of stacked papers is causing extra set-off on these copies.\r\n\r\nBased on our observations we believe that any copies above the 21,000 mark would not have this extra set-off as all the press check copies appear good.\r\n\r\nI have kept all the press check copies if you require these to show the client. \r\n\r\nOn a separate note I would also like to suggest the client supply their Ad with overprint black text which would assist in achieving a better result of text not getting a halo of white space. This may not be possible due to the required total CMYK ink breakdown of 230% \r\n', 'Closed', '', 'possible 21,000', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1152, 1318238692, NULL, 1317477600, '1', 13, 1, 'E', '1', '', '', 'TPG', '', 1, 7, 1, 9, 'Client is complaining about the reproduction of their TPG ad within Shop Smart, page 1.\r\nThe print is meant to be purple but instead is blue.\r\nCan we find out how many were affected, all copies here are dark blue\r\ncolour breakdown is Cyan 60% Magenta 100% yellow 0% black 30%', 1, '1', 'Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nI have gone through the Shop Smart QC copies collected every 10,000 copies during production.\r\n\r\nThe job started with good colour balance, at approximately the 213,000 check copy the colour balance started to drift. Some of the check copies have the same appearance as your sample. The grey beans appear to have a Cyan hue to them indicating that Cyan has increased causing the purple to shift towards blue\r\n\r\nThis job ran on two presses\r\n\r\nC press ran a total of 155,072 copies\r\nE press ran a total of 509,814 copies\r\n\r\nThe sample you provided was from E press; therefore I feel approximately 296,814 copies have shifted towards a blueish look as per your sample\r\n\r\nThe press manger will discuss this complaint with the press crew responsible \r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you require these check copies\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1153, 1322604388, NULL, 1322485200, '1', 1, 8, 'E', '', 'Alan Price', '', '', '', 1, 16, 3, 2, 'There was a problem with the above papers today. The paper was folded out of alignment such that the cut of the right hand side of the paper was touching the border of the main page photo – no leading border at all. The bigger problem is the stories on the inside are missing the start of the page as you look from the left. Some very unhappy people!\r\n\r\n', 1, '1', 'Cut-offs driving out', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1154, 1326688916, NULL, 1326632400, '1', 3, 1, 'F', '1, 28, 8 & 21 throughout', '', '', 'Broadwalk EMPIRE', '', 0, 7, 1, 5, 'mx have complained about the copies they have received in the office particurally the front page and back cyan and magenta are over a mm out from the black and yellow.\r\npage 8 & 21 heavyblotching of cyan at top of form,\r\nhickeys on page 25 through ad.\r\nregistration issues on p4 & 25, 9& 20, 10& 19, 12&17 as well.', 1, '3', 'Hi Mark\r\n\r\nWe have received and inspected your sample paper, speaking with Press Shift Manager and Team Leader they feel this is a restart copy, at 1.30pm the press stopped to replace a cracked plate. On occasions after restart when going to good copy the press releases some copies which are still settling in, unfortunately this is about the time when the last bulk would be loaded onto the Holt Street truck. \r\n\r\nThe press crew on the day had not called their QC copies which make up part of the 4 bulk which are delivered to Holt Street each day. \r\n\r\nAfter inspecting all our press check copies which I sent you, there is no evidence of poor registration or ink dag, and we feel that affected copies would be no more than 100-200 copies \r\n\r\nCorrective Action Taken: \r\nThe Shift Manager and Team Leader will address this with the press crew responsible and ensure the process of sending QC’s before or by 15,000 copies is followed by all press crews.\r\n\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  |  Quality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '100-200', '1', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1155, 1327297669, NULL, 1327064400, '2', 17, 1, 'D', '49', 'Classifieds', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 11, 'In the 3rd & 4th coloum halfway down there is black image missing. This is a classified page. Is the whole run like this?', 1, '7', 'All check copies are affected. I think Gary is on the money with the cause. Blankets were checked for holes (found nothing) and there is no record of blankets being changed friday night and or on the weekend. Therefore the image must have been missing on the plate.\r\n\r\nI will forward this onto Simon and Garth to notify the crew for feedback and future reference\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n', 'Closed', '', 'Whole run', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1156, 1327893999, NULL, 1327669200, '2', 17, 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 17, 'low res image due to artist blowing size.', 1, '1', 'this was a test', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1157, 1327965970, NULL, 1327928400, '1', 1, 3, 'E', '30', '2012 Gourmet Guide', '', '', '', 0, 3, 1, 5, 'Cornella from News Advantage has rang complaining about the registration on page 30, my office QC copies show that the registration is out also. Can you check if the whole run was like this. Thanks. Lee Dunks', 1, '1', 'Waiting for rep''s check copies to arrive at Chullora, we can see some evidence of registration on some copies. Need to establish how bad Rep’s copy is.\r\n\r\nLee Dunks is also investigating the specification of supplied material, the white type appears to be below spec??\r\n\r\nHi Lee, \r\n\r\nSample arrive the registration problem seen in this sample is similar to our check copies, this is evident throughout the run. As previously discussed the white type is very thin and the black text on the ATLANTIS seafood restaurant ad is colour in 4 colour black. \r\n\r\nAfter your investigation noted that the type is below our specifications, white type this small is very hard to control on press and therefore recommend the creative be supplied using a larger type size also single colour black type. Supplying files to the correct specifications greatly assists when reproducing these small Ads.\r\n\r\nThis being an internally designed advert I feel we can control the specifications, designing adverts that print to the expectations of our clients. \r\n\r\nRegards Gary\r\n\r\n\r\nFrom Lee Dunks\r\nGary\r\n\r\nThe type was not created within our specifications. I will be talking to Corinella Asaad from News Advantage regarding this, which they have already been spoken to about this issues before with Scott Draper.\r\n\r\nLee Dunks \r\nOperations - Quality Control \r\n\r\n\r\nRegards\r\nGary Woodside  \r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 1),
(1158, 1328056980, NULL, 1328014800, '2', 16, 1, 'D', '1', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 7, 'Looking at this weeks papers so far the mastheads on the front cover are inconsistant. If you compare Parramatta and Liverpool, Liverpool looks great, Parra almost looks Orange. We need the mastheads to be more consistant and this weeks Liverpool Leader is a good guide to the colour/density we would like to achieve. Thanks. Lee', 1, '7', 'Lee,\r\n\r\nLooking into this one. having trouble finding check copies. Was printed on Delta which is not usually the case. Will speak to Garth and wait for a response from arvo press crew.\r\n\r\nSteve\r\n\r\nSteve , Lee\r\n\r\nThere was a check copy in the pigeon hole which was signed off and colour masthead looked fine.\r\n\r\nThe time stamp copies that were recorded were accidently thrown out by N/S.\r\n\r\nThe masthead is lower in magenta then what was checked and signed off too which all press personal will pay closer attention when in production to ensure quality remains consistenace.\r\n\r\nGarth', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1159, 1331093951, NULL, 1331038800, '2', 7, 1, 'E', '3, 25', 'Liverpool Council', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 11, 'Page 3, 25 there is no black image on page. Looks like a start up copy, but this shouldn\\''t have gone out.\r\nThis is about the email i sent earlier.\r\nPlease have a look at the check copies.\r\nI will drop off my copy tomorrow morning and we can have a look together.\r\nThanks, Lee.', 1, '7', 'Black Ink failure had occurred mid run. Press crew immediately shut down press and all publishing lines. 21 bulk were removed from truck. Managers had thought they had pulled back all affected copies but less than a few bulk have slipped out.\r\n\r\nlack of info in Chullora Report will also be discussed with press crew as News Local staff would have been already aware of the problem.', 'Closed', '', '<200', '0', '1', '0', 1, 1),
(1160, 1332291621, NULL, 1332248400, '2', 1, 1, 'F', '70 - 3', '', '', 'Brian Hilton', '', 0, 11, 2, 2, 'The Cyan is non-existent on the bottom half of the page resulting in a \\"pink\\" reproduction of the vehicles. ', 1, '19', 'Due to repeated failures during the check procedure, the Brian Hilton ad ran for the entire South edition.\r\nThe press crew has been counselled as a whole, and the individual on the colour desk will take part in ongoing coaching.', 'Closed', '', '62,600', '1', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1173, 1334861415, NULL, 1335016800, '1', 9, 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 14, 'Colour bars on Escape are covered by image, restrict the use of denso. Samples sent via internal mail.', 1, '1', 'Problem with plate template colour bar not knocking out image, Plate template needs to be modified.\r\n\r\nSteve Mather will amend these templates\r\n\r\nGary Woodside \r\nQuality and Continuous Improvement Manager\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1174, 1334863343, NULL, 1335016800, '1', 13, 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 1, 2, 'incorrect dateline on page 22 of Shop Smart', 1, '11', 'logged with editorial', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1175, 1335411642, NULL, 1334844000, '1', 3, 1, 'D', '1, 24', '', '', 'McDonalds', '', 1, 7, 1, 9, 'I have received a print complaint regarding the reproduction of the McDonald ads in the mX edition of the 20Th April page 1 and 24,\r\nThe complaint is the red is very light on the front and the bottom of page 24 not to their expectations.\r\nCan we find out numbers etc, D press\r\nCopies in the internal mail\r\n', 1, '20', 'Hi Mark,\r\nThese copies seem to be start up or re-start copies. All our QC\\''s are ok and have been sent into Holt St for inspection.\r\n\r\nCrew have been given the appropriate feedback.\r\n\r\nSteve', 'Closed', '', '<200', '1', '0', '0', 1, 0),
