(1177, 1335739530, NULL, 1335621600, '1', 13, 6, 'all', '36', '', '', 'News Life Media Ad ', '', 0, 1, 3, 16, 'My copy of paper on the weekend appeared to have corrupt News Life Media Ad on page 36 text looks corrupt.\r\n\r\n Checking Arkitex and copies off C press this morning it is evident that this ran for the entire run as there are no signs of a revised page.\r\n\r\nGary Woodside \r\nQuality and Continuous Improvement Manager \r\n', 1, '3', 'Ad was back doored from town, didn\\''t come through QC. Have advised Marketing all material in future needs to go through QC.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1178, 1335979256, NULL, 1336226400, '1', 9, 1, 'E', 'Page 1 of the mini book', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 14, 'Page 1 of mini book not lining up, out by approx 8mm, contacted ECD then Scott Draper on the 1300 number, unfortunately unable to rectifiy.', 1, '3', 'Re-visited this issue in the morning with Scott Draper & Gary Woodside and problem was fixed.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1179, 1336159612, NULL, 1336140000, '1', 2, 1, 'E', '8', '', '', 'Dick Langs Bush Pilots', '', 0, 23, 3, 16, 'Part of the add was missing for Dick Langs Bush pilots, Peter Raishbrook from E Press spotted it. Calls were made to ECD and Aus editorial. Ecd were able to correct for the next edition.', 1, '3', 'Issue was fixed', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1181, 1336492946, NULL, 1336485600, '2', 5, 1, 'E', '26 and 27', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 12, 'Press crews noticed after approx 25,000 copies that on page 26 and 27 the were adds that had been duplicated, the 1300 number was called and Lee Dunks tried to log on and have a look, Lee was unable to fix and directed press to continue running.', 1, '3', 'Advised Press to keep running as i wasn\\''t 100% sure what ad was supposed to run. When i checked with Layouts the ads were doubled up on purpose to fill some spots.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1183, 1336956775, NULL, 1336744800, '1', 1, 3, 'D Press', '64', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 11, 'Brett Addams found that page 64 had several other letters and numbers before the page number 64. The QC hot line was contacted and we were instructed to continue with production as it couldn\\''t be fixed at the time. State edition was not affected.', 1, '3', 'Advised Press to keep running', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1184, 1336957151, NULL, 1336658400, '1', 2, 1, 'E Press', '38', '', '', '', '', 0, 29, 3, 17, 'Matt Harvey found missing image in Cowboys team list. Contacted QC hot line, instructed to continue with production.', 1, '3', 'I received this call and i contacted Ray Briggs who contacted Editorial in town to fix.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1185, 1337049165, NULL, 1337004000, '2', 20, 1, 'C Press', '42', '', '', '', '', 0, 29, 3, 16, 'C Press Afternoon shift (Paul Hoffman) stopped press to corrupt page. Advert sitting on top of editorial (story). QC hot line contacted and page was repaired. ', 1, '3', 'Layout issue caused this error. New procedure set in place for layouts.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1186, 1337180940, NULL, 1337090400, '2', 9, 1, 'D', '11', '', '', '', '', 0, 27, 3, 11, 'Folio was actually correct but the News,Whats on,Lifestyle,Classifieds,Sport was incorrect, it stated the book went up to 80 pages when it was only 60 pages. This has happened several times now.', 1, '3', 'Advised Press to keep running', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1187, 1337213925, NULL, 1337349600, '1', 12, 1, '', '10 Mini Book', '', '', '', '', 0, 20, 3, 14, 'Please note this is The Best Weekend not Homes. Page 10 of the Mini Book has a colour bar inside the printed area. The crew moved the image as much they could but still had some visual damage of around 1-2mm.', 1, '14', 'Material was supplied late, at the wrong size, with the crop information supplied as image and process as best as the material would allow. The file was attempted to be fixed and processed in the morning, however the new file errored loading into Arkitex and the original had to print for the enitire run', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1188, 1337227304, NULL, 1337263200, '2', 2, 2, 'D', '43', '', '', '', '', 0, 28, 3, 12, 'Page nine from news section repeated in cars guide section (sheet number 43) . Rectified by remaking page 43 of South edition. 2580 copies dumped & deinserted.', 1, '3', 'Supplied correct file once notified.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1189, 1337228264, NULL, 1337090400, '2', 9, 1, 'D Press', 'Page 11 & Page 28', '', '', '', '', 0, 29, 3, 11, 'We encounted incorrect folios on pages 11 & 28 on Northern Districts, we rang Cumberland at 12:15 am and spoke to Manny to enquire if the pages can be altered the response was no and \r\nwas told to proceed with production.\r\n', 1, '3', 'Advised Press to keep running', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1191, 1337625440, NULL, 1337695200, '2', 5, 1, 'D', '17', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 11, 'The section pointers on the top of page 17 are incorrect, its a 32 page book but pointers go up to 80 pages. This is two weeks in a row now. G.Arneil spotted this fault.', 1, '3', 'Advised Press to keep running', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1192, 1337646929, NULL, 1337608800, '1', 1, 1, 'E', '1', '', '', '', '', 0, 11, 2, 7, 'the papers that we received into the building from E press have a very distinct purple hue to them compared to the D press papers. I will send Gary Woodside a copy of both via internal mail.', 1, '20', 'Scott,\r\n\r\nOn Inspection of check copies, we found the first 2 similar to your copy i.e. the first make-ready QC check, and the 10000 check copy. All other check copies were at the required cyan densisty.I will pass this onto the Arvo/nightshift crew involved for some feedback.\r\n\r\nSteve', 'Closed', '', '10-15000', '0', '1', '1', 1, 0),
(1195, 1337650726, NULL, 1337090400, '1', 3, 1, 'C', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 7, 1, 7, 'Last Wednesday 16/5/12 I believe the press ran out of ink during the mX run? We have an advertising client who is claiming their ad looks washed out and not printed to their expectation.\r\n\r\nAre we able to determine when in the run the press ran out and what copies in the run would have been affected? \r\n\r\nApologies if you have already received an email from Stacey about this. She has been away ill, and the client is pressing for some feedback. The client is also sending us the copies of mX that they picked up.\r\n\r\nAny information that you can provide would be greatly appreciated.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMark', 1, '20', 'Mark,\r\n\r\nThe press had some ink issues that day on Charlie. The reliabilty team were working on the ink pumps which caused the failure. The crew had become aware of the situation due to \\"ink level low alarms\\" and when the ducts would no longer fill the press was pulled up between 12:56 and 13:01. Reliability then fixed the issue and the press was on it\\''s way again. \r\nThere is some evidence of this at the 10000 check copy stage but none before or after.\r\nI estimate that no more than 2000 copies would be affected during this stage as I believe it would have been during the press slowing down and stopping when they ran out of ink.\r\nIf you require any thing else please let me know.\r\n\r\nSteve\r\n', 'Closed', '', '<2000', '1', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1197, 1337800876, NULL, 1337781600, '1', 1, 1, 'All', '34-55', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 14, 'Page 34- 55 is a double page spread. The bottom of the page was sitting lower than the cross hairs and was setting off onto the next page, editorial were contacted and they fixed the page, however this page didn\\''t go onto till presses picked up the metro dropins. Jim Warren from E press identified this issue.', 1, '3', 'Looks like this issue was fixed so im closing this log.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1198, 1337816331, NULL, 1337695200, '2', 17, 1, 'D', '11', 'Raine & Horne', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'Raine & Horne have complained about their ad on Page 11 of the Real Estate section in Wednesday\\''s Manly Daily. It looks washed out. You can compare it to last weeks ad in Manly Daily Wednesday Page 5 of the Real Estate section. File supllied looks ok and i\\''ve printed a proof of to compare. I will send this in the internal mail attention to Gary Woodside. Thanks, Lee', 1, '20', 'Lee,\r\n\r\nI have inspected all check copies and unfortunately all are affected with a very poor colour balance on this page. I will forward this onto the Afternoon Managers for them to take the appropriate action with the crew involved.\r\n\r\nSteve', 'Closed', '', 'Full Run', '0', '1', '0', 1, 0),
(1199, 1337816771, NULL, 1337781600, '1', 1, 4, 'D', '1', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 7, 'The origin image on the Metro editon cover has a Magenta hue compared to the first edition. The blue jerseys look purple?? We had the same issue on Tuesdays edition with the D press copies compared to the E press copies.', 1, '1', 'Press crews have been made aware to keep an eye on dark blue which can tend to shift purple.\r\n\r\nGary', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1200, 1337902669, NULL, 1338040800, '1', 16, 1, 'D and F', '10 and 11', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 13, 'Smart Shopper pages 10 and 11.\r\n\r\nRenovation Boys ads were duplicated acrosss these pages. Call made to Scott Draper who advised to keep running unless told otherwise and it may have been to fill in a space.\r\nIf this is the case it may be wise to inform Chullora of these duplications in the futureto minmise confusion.\r\n\r\nSteve\r\n', 1, '3', 'Press advised 2 ads were doubled up, I looked on Ad Watch and both bookings had the same material so advised press to keep running as i couldn\\''t find the correct file.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1201, 1338421245, NULL, 1338300000, '2', 10, 1, 'C', '19-34', '', '', 'Paradise Kitchens, Castle Hill Tavern, Pitt Town Sports', '', 1, 3, 2, 11, 'Not sure if there is no yellow image on the plate or no Yellow ink but on pages 19-34 there is no Yellow ink staring 7cm from the top to 7cm from the bottom, so almost the whole page. Was the whole run like this? Thanks, Lee', 1, '20', 'Lee,\r\nI have inspected check copies and all are affected by a very poor density of yellow. There are no reports of any printing faults on the press.\r\nI have spoken to Ian Ford and he and Scott Haywood will pass this onto the nightshift crew tomorrow morning and take the appropriate course of action. \r\n\r\nSteve\r\n\r\nAll,\r\nIn regards to the customer complaint on Rouse Hill Times 30 May 2012. \r\n \r\nAfter discussions with the responsible crew it was agreed we have to be more vigilant especially on the short runs. \r\n \r\nThough not being 100% of the cause it was decided the most likely cause was that we have been having issues with the ink sitting back in the ducts. Usually the cyan & magenta and they are now regularly stirred prior to each production. We predict this is what happened in this instance on the yellow.\r\n \r\nWe are now placing as standard pre-run procedure that all ink ducts are to be stirred not just the cyan magenta.\r\n \r\nLachlan\r\n\r\n', 'Closed', '', 'Whole Run 18,000', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1202, 1338854595, NULL, 1338904800, '2', 6, 1, 'C Press', '33', '', '', 'Telstra', '', 0, 28, 3, 16, 'Page 33 Ted Barrett found 1/2 page telstra ad had low resolution or pixelating image & type offering unreadable details.(10,000 copies printed prior to fix).', 1, '3', 'Fixed file and supplied a high res version to Chullora Press.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1203, 1338951163, NULL, 1338472800, '1', 1, 4, 'D', '30-31', '', '', 'Hyundai', '', 1, 3, 2, 2, 'I received an email from this client regarding the reproduction of their ad, double page spread, that ran in Friday\\''s Tele. They have complained the text in the background is washed out and unreadable. I have looked at the file and the text is a 20% tint of black which probably should have been raised with them, but it looks like the 20% dot didn\\''t hold. My QC copie page 30 is very hard to read, right hand page is a little darker. Can you check your copies and see if it\\''s the whole run. Thanks', 1, '20', 'Lee,\r\n\r\nLooks as though this is an incorrect screen. Gary is looking into this as there is sufficient black on the page.\r\n\r\nSteve\r\n\r\nJob has printed as files supplied, artwork has ghosted black type running being images. This appears to be a design aspect and not intended to be completely legible,  Gary', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1204, 1338951524, NULL, 1339164000, '1', 12, 1, '', '15, 16, 17, 18', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 2, 'Leanne Crocker and Charles Miranda have complained that pages 15, 16, 17 & 18 are all washed out and a little Yellow. My QC copies look fine, i guess the Holt street copies didn\\''t. Please check your copies and see if this is evident in the run. Thanks', 1, '20', 'Lee,\r\n\r\nI inspected all check copies and they are OK. If you can I would like to see an affected copy, as I\\''m sure Parramatta and Holt St get the same bulk.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nSteve', 'Closed', '', '??', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1205, 1339023163, NULL, 1338904800, '2', 9, 1, '', 'Page 56', '', '', '', '', 0, 23, 3, 11, 'Pg 56 on bottom of page. Pg 60 on top of pg. Called 1300 number given the OK to run on.', 1, '5', 'Editorial not updating folio straps due to copying pages from other ranges.\r\neditorial have been told not to dupe pages.', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
