(1255, 1351560672, NULL, 1351515600, '2', 15, 1, 'C', '13', '', '', '', '', 0, 3, 2, 7, 'Page 13 of the main book on all editions has alot of black ink through the editorial images and Red banner at top. If you turn to page 15 you will see what the red banner should look like. Please check copies and see if it\\''s the entire run. thanks', 1, '1', 'After further investigation this error was possibly corruption in Arkitex, The same job was reloaded and the form 13 appeared normal.\r\n\r\nAt the time of the complaint the form 13 in Arkitex had excessive black applied to the file affecting coloured panels and the pictures\r\n\r\nSteve London from AGFA reloaded the log files for this job and noted that at the time of production this job was reloaded multiple times, we believe this could have possibly corrupted the job. Unfortunately we have no screen shots of the corrupt form for Steve to get more understanding of the problem. \r\n\r\nWe can only keep any eye out in case this occurs again\r\n\r\nGary Woodside \r\nQuality and Continuous Improvement Manager \r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 0),
