(1258, 1352094009, NULL, 1352034000, '1', 3, 1, 'D', 'all pages', '', '', 'mx', '', 0, 7, 1, 16, 'I have fielded a complaint regarding the quality of papers received to mX, the copies have heavy setup and transfer horizontal marking across the full width ofevery page at about 11cms approx 1cm in thickness.\r\nI am putting paper in internal mail addressed to Ian Ford', 1, '32', 'Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nThank you for the sample copies.\r\n\r\nIn regards to the heavy set-off marking all pages. I have checked the press QC copies and there is no evidence of the marking. This then means the marking has come from the stacking cell crush roller and the entire run would have been effected.\r\n\r\nThe complaint has highlighted the need for an additional check at the stacking cells and a review of our Holt Street copies procedure. These changes will commence as of today.    \r\n\r\nIf you require any further information please let me know.\r\n', 'Closed', '', '103414', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
