(1369, 1378167386, NULL, 1377784800, '2', 2, 2, 'C', '22', 'Ulimate Steel Building System', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 6, 'Client is unhappy with registration of their add. Hard to read web details. This ad is in both editions (south & north) and both pages are out of registration', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\nThe Central Coast Express South and North check copies had been reviewed and all the North copies do show the advert difficult to read, due to the registration. \r\nThe quality of the South check copies improved, however the advert in question is still difficult to read. Other adverts on the same page contain reverse type which is clearly readable but Aussteel web site details are still difficult to read. Is it possible that it’s the way the ad was supplied?\r\nEach time a registration complaint is recorded into the QC log it has been communicated to the press crews, to highlight the importance of WHY there needs to be quality papers produced. Also, each time there’s a reported incident the crews involved receive the feedback and that feedback is entered into the feedback performance log, which tracks individual staff members work performance.\r\nWe are still working on replacing full units of blankets that are above their expected impression count. There has also been an announcement for the plate room to receive new plate benders. Both of these points are steps to improve the quality of the products that are produced at the print centre.             \r\nIf you require any further information please contact me.\r\nRegards,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '90,000', '1', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1370, 1378167619, NULL, 1377784800, '2', 21, 1, '', '36', 'Wiseberry RE', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 6, 'Client has complained their ads look blurry. Ads appear on page 34 to 37. My copy 35 & 36 are out of registration but mainly 36 and it\\''s only the top of the page.', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\nThe Central Coast Real Estate check copies show page 36 out of registration for the entire production. \r\nThe smaller reverse type at the top of the page gives the impression that only the top of the page is out. However on closer inspection, the whole page and every page printed from that cylinder is out of registration. The press reports have also been reviewed and there’s no indication of any technical issues during the production. Further investigation with the press crew is required to determine the cause, this will take place tonight with a root cause to be communicated.\r\nRegards,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '64,000', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
