(1410, 1383272617, NULL, 1382965200, '2', 24, 1, '', '80-81', 'Belle Property', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'client isnt happy with the colour difference with their 2 ads side by side. The greens are not matching. Is the whole run like this?', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\nAfter reviewing the QC check copies on Hill Shire Real Estate, all copies are showing a colour variation on page 80 and 81.\r\nQI press control system would usually reduce or close to eliminate colour variation from page to page. However, a software patch upgrade was installed early last week, this patch failed causing all tiff images for panorama plate jobs to be lost. This means Hill Shire Real Estate was produced with QI in manual. The press crew involved, are required to monitor and adjust ink settings to correct densities, when QI is in auto or manual.\r\nThis production will be discussed with the press crew, with feedback to be logged against the press crew involved.\r\nIf you require any further information, please do not hesitate to let me know.\r\nRegards,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '67,831', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1411, 1383272781, NULL, 1383051600, '2', 16, 1, 'C', '54-55', 'Tracy Roberts', '', '', '', 1, 3, 2, 7, 'Client is complaining their Blue colour has printed purple on page 54, but yet perfect on page 55. Also head shot on 54 is very red, their is alot more Magenta on bottom 1/4 of page 54 than wat there should be. Is whole run like this?', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\nAfter reviewing the QC check copies on Parramatta, all copies are showing a colour variation on page 54 and 55.\r\nQI press control system would usually reduce or close to eliminate colour variation from page to page. The press report indicates the crew had a quality issue with the QI system, resulting in the system being switched to manual. The press crew involved, are required to monitor and adjust ink settings to correct densities, when QI is in auto or manual.\r\nThis production will be discussed with the press crew, with feedback to be logged against the press crew involved.\r\nIf you require any further information, please do not hesitate to let me know.\r\nRegards,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '82,311', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
(1412, 1383277591, NULL, 1382619600, '1', 4, 1, 'E', '17,111', 'News Emporium', '', 'Micallef, Paul ', '', 1, 16, 3, 10, 'Hi Rade\r\n\r\nOnce again Sportsman has been sent out with poor quality printing and it happens to be on the Cox Plate formguide.  There are 25 copies sitting at Sans Souci waiting to be purchased.  It has also been reported that six pages in the Midweek Sportsman were also of poor quality.\r\n', 1, '16', 'The quality problems on page 17 and 111 as per attached photos were caused by variation in the black ink and water balance window at the start of the Sportsman printing. The water and ink balance window has always been a feel thing for a printer. To ensure we are improving our printing quality, refreshment training for setting the water ink balance at the start of the printing process will be conducted as well as feasibility to amend the start-up procedure to reduce the risk associated with this problem.\r\n\r\nFor some time, we are battling the hickey issue in Sydney Print Centre. A hickey is any particle that sticks to the blanket or plate that transfers an imperfection to the printed page. Usually they are a dot with the ring around it and if they are left uncontrolled, they cause as massive amounts of waste. For this reason we’ve increased the original fount level of 2.2% to 2.5% across all presses.  At the morning hicky meeting we decided to return the original fount level of 2.2% as the improper printing ink / water balance can be correlated with the fount level.\r\n\r\nThe complaint has been presented to Production Leaders who in turn has informed all press teams as a training exercise. Also, recently established quality initiatives, particularly in the press hall, with a number of process improvements have been initiated to prevent recurrence of this issue.\r\n', 'Closed', '', '', '0', '1', '0', 1, 0),
