(1505, 1416438578, NULL, 1416402000, '1', 1, 8, 'C', 'all', '', '', 'The tele', '', 0, 7, 1, 27, 'Heavy black ink laydown throughout the tele stand out page 1.27 bold text is bleeding, consistently over 1.10 throughout rest- this was a QC copy sent into Holt street', 1, '32', 'Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nApologies, this information should have been sent through yesterday.\r\n\r\nAll press check copies of the Daily Telegraph (publication date - 20/11/14) across both presses have been review.\r\n\r\nD Press check copies don\\''t show the same density readings or excessive black ink laydown, D Press produced 123,816 copies.\r\n\r\nC Press check copies don\\''t show the same density readings or excessive black ink laydown up until the 60,000 check copy. Each check copy after 60,000 does show the same density readings or excessive black ink laydown. C Press copies produced (With excessive ink) - 94,040 copies.\r\n\r\nThe press crews involved have been counselled. The DT on C Press was the first full production to trial a new formula of black ink. The printer adjusted the density to improve the print but adjusted the density to high and failed to pick up the quality issue.\r\n\r\nShaw, Scott and Nathan are working very closely with the ink suppliers to rectify the black laydown issue. Samples of the trial are being sent into Holt Street every few days, Nathan will now include yourself on that list to receive the samples.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you require any further information.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nIan           ', 'Closed', '', '94040', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1506, 1416439410, NULL, 1416402000, '1', 2, 4, '', 'Many', '', '', 'The Aus', '', 0, 7, 1, 9, 'Colour balance issues through out, magenta over 1.0 on most pages, cyan just under 1.0 on many pages, set off evident throughout stand out page red on page 4 from page 5', 1, '32', 'Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nApologies, this information should have been sent through yesterday.\r\n\r\nAll press check copies of The Australian (publication date - 20/11/14) have been reviewed.\r\n\r\nThe Press check copies do show the same magenta and cyan density readings as you mentioned. The set off however would be because of the jaw fold being in-line with a lot of adverts and the increase in ink density.\r\n\r\nThe crew did report an ink balance issue with magenta during the production, however the press check copies and density readings have been used to debrief the press crew involved.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you require any further information.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '41186', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1507, 1416794335, NULL, 1416661200, '1', 13, 1, 'E', '71 & 82', 'TPG & Sunday Tele House Ad', '', 'TPG & Sunday Tele House Ad', '', 0, 32, 3, 17, 'Missing image was discovered on page 71 (TPG Ad) and follow up page 82 (Sunday Tele House Ad).\r\n', 1, '32', 'Hi Mark,\r\nE Press Sunday Tele press check copies were being checked for black ink performance this morning and missing image was discovered on page 71 (TPG Ad) and follow up page 82 (Sunday Tele House Ad).\r\nRoot cause - tissue paper covering the plate in the polaris during the imaging stage in the plateroom. Copies effected - 156,247. \r\nUnfortunately, the start up checks have missed the missing image, this will be discussed with the press crews involved in the form of performance management.  \r\nIf you require any further information please contact me.\r\nThank you,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '156,247', '0', '1', '1', 1, 0),
(1508, 1416875848, NULL, 1416488400, '1', 2, 4, '', '27', '', '', '12th Floor', '', 1, 3, 1, 7, 'Customer\\''s copy shows the magenta in the colour bar has a low ink density. Colour of ad printed brown, should be more of a red/brown. My copy is fine. Can you check your copies and see how many affected? Thanks', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\nAll press check copies for The Australian (Publication date 25/11/2014) from D Press have been reviewed.\r\nNone of the check copies show signs of magenta ink balance issues on page 27 (12th Floor ad). Nor did the press crew report any ink balance issues throughout the production. In reviewing the production report, the only stops during the run were for edition changes (one for Canberra and one for AF).\r\nThe clients copy could be a re-start copy, where the copies were released to early on a press re-start. If this was the case a maximum of 100 copies would have been effected.\r\nAs always, the press check copies are available for the Ad rep and client if required. They can be used to compare the client copy with the rest of the production. \r\nIf you require any further information please contact me.\r\nThanks,\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '100', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
