(1554, 1442965501, NULL, 1442930400, '1', 2, 4, '', '1 and 18', '', '', 'Internal management', '', 0, 7, 1, 9, 'Management received home delivered paper-mosman, front cover is is poor- lacking color- Yellow down slightly through the centre of page pg1 but magenta considerably down spreading from page 18 across 75% of page 1- as low as .55.', 1, '32', 'Hi Mark,\r\n\r\nAll check copies have been review and it shows all 39,000 copies to be affected.\r\n\r\nThe press crew that ran the production reported technical issues with QI so QI was switched to manual. As this information wasn\\''t reported or escalated though the correct channels, leaders were unaware of the technical issues and Reliability wasn\\''t contacted to investigate.\r\n\r\nPerformance conversations will take place with the press crews involved.\r\n\r\nIf you require any further information please contact me.\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n\r\nIan', 'Closed', '', '39,000', '0', '0', '1', 1, 0),
(1555, 1443406214, NULL, 1443362400, '1', 1, 8, 'C', '28', '', '', 'Commonwealth Bank', '', 1, 3, 1, 30, 'See image attached, there is a white (faded) line throughout the ad, I\\''m not sure what it is, but it\\''s not the actual ad, even the editorial text next to it is also faded.', 1, '32', 'Hi Lee,\r\n\r\nAfter reviewing all check copies from last nights C Press Telegraph production, it\\''s been determined that the white faded lines is a form of image wear.\r\n\r\nThe wear starts to appear in the country edition and is evident throughout the production. Based on when the wear is noticed within the check copies, overall affect copies - 120,000.\r\n\r\nThe press crew stopped production at 1:20am to replace the page due to wear, however the check copies show that the replacement should have happened a lot sooner. Leaders will be conducting performance conversations with press crews involved.\r\n\r\nThis plate position on C press had a blanket change late last week due to noticeable wear. Upon inspection today the blanket tension, condition and roller settings are ok and will be monitored during this afternoon\\''s Bankstown production.\r\n\r\nAs normal the press check copies are available if required, if you require any further information please contact me.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nIan  ', 'Closed', '', '120000', '0', '0', '0', 1, 0),
